Yes air trapped in ice that is thousands and millions of years old can migrate upwards slightly through the ice before it's permanently locked in. In the locations where ice core samples are usually taken, snowfall is low. So small movements in upward distance can appear as 100s of years of lag. You're referring mainly to an error in the time axis rather than CO2 concentation.
